        "question": "How do I authenticate with this skill?",
        "answer": "Copy an authenticated curl command from your browser DevTools Network tab and import it using the import-curl command. The skill extracts cookies from the curl and stores them in your home directory."
      },
      {
        "question": "What happens when my cookies expire?",
        "answer": "When you get a 401 error on private endpoints, re-import cookies by copying a fresh authenticated curl from your browser and running the import-curl command again."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I search for papers by title?",
        "answer": "Title search is unreliable. Use graph-batch with arXiv or DOI identifiers instead for accurate paper resolution. The search/match endpoint may return wrong fuzzy matches."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I add papers to my Library?",
        "answer": "Use folder-add with the paperId, paperTitle, and folderIds parameters. First resolve the paper ID using graph-batch if you only have the arXiv ID."
